          "explanation": "Each number should represent diameter of instrument in 100th of millimeter at the tip. \nFor example, a No. 25 K file shall have 0.25 mm at D1 and 0.57 mm (0.25 + 0.32) at D2. \nThese sizes ensure a constant increase in taper, i.e. 0.02 mm/mm of the instrument regardless of the size."
