          "text": "A 30 years old male reported with chief complaint of  constant radiating, gnawing pain that is intensified by eating spicy foods and chewing. He also reported a \"metallic\" foul taste and an excessive amount of \"pasty\"saliva. A general examination revealed fever and increased pulse rate. Intra-oral examination showed punched-out, crater like depressions at the crest of the interdental gingival papillae, covered by a gray pseudomembranous slough, in the upper anterior teeth.\n\nThe most likely infection is",
