          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "The blank design employed by the Endo Sequence file is a triangle with alternating contact points (ACP) along the instrument's ,hunk. The Endo Sequence file undergoes electropolishing and the result is visible in its mirror-like finish that remains sharper longer and mays cleaner during use.\nAbout RACE:\nDesign of the reamer with alternating  cutting edges (RACE): twisted areas alternate with straight parts. The NM surface is treated chemically resulting in an obviously smoother surface than other instruments.\nAbout 3:\n\nPositive rake angle\nVariable helical flute angle\nPeripheral blade relief\nThird radial land\nVariable core diameter\nSafe-ended tip\nWide radial lands\n\nAbout Lightspeed:\nThe LightSpeed root canal instrument has a noncutting tip and a short blade. The shaft is smooth, nontapered and very flexible. Instruments have physical resemblance with Gates Glidden drills. Also remember that term '12 peck e is associated with lightspeed instruments."
