          "explanation": "TUBEROUS SCLEROSIS Cutaneous manifestations Angiofibromas (previously called adenoma sebaceum):- Most frequent manifestation, seen in almost 90% of patients. Appear in childhood and enlarge at pubey (hence the misnomer \"sebaceum\"). Reddish brown, smooth, dome-shaped papules with telangiectasis. Symmetrically, on nose, nasolabial folds, cheeks. Ref:- Neena khanna; pg num:-32,33",
