          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Water fluoridation depends on the temperature in that area and body weight.\nGalagan formula for ﬂuoride: \nThis is usually calculated by the formula given by Galagan and Vermillion in 1957.\nPpm of F ‾= - 0.038 +0.0062 t temperature in Fahrenheit.\n‘E’ is the estimated daily water intake for children in ounces per pound of body weight.\n‘t’ is the yearly mean of the daily maximum temperature in Fahrenheit.\nEssentials of preventive and community dentistry \nSoben Peter \n5th edition"
