          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Static mixing — A technique of transforming two fluid (or paste-like) materials into a homogeneous mixture without mechanical stirring; it requires a device that forces two streams of material into  a mixer cylinder, such that as the streams move through the mixer, while the stationary elements in the mixer continuously blend the materials.\nKey Concept\nA technique of transforming two fluid (or paste-like) materials into a homogeneous mixture without mechanical stirring is called static mixing.\nRef: Phillip’s Science of Dental Materials ed 12 pg 152"
