          "explanation": "Rakosi- Jarabak analysis\nThe sum of  posterior angles i.e. the cranial base (N–S–Ar), articular (S–Ar–Go), and gonial angles (Ar–Go–Me)> 396 degrees indicates clockwise direction of growth i.e. vertical growth.\nThe sum of  posterior angles i.e. the cranial base (N–S–Ar), articular (S–Ar–Go), and gonial angles (Ar–Go–Me)< 396 degrees indicates anticlockwise direction of growth i.e. horizontal growth."
