          "explanation": "SCATTER DIAGRAM\n\nAlso known as ‘Correlation diagram’ or ‘Dot diagram’.\nIs used to depict ‘correlation (relationship) between 2 quantitative variables’.\n‘Vertical axis in scatter diagram: should be the dependent or the outcome variable.\nIn a scatter diagram, 2 imaginary lines are drawn along the distribution of dots/scatter."
