          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Necrobiosis lipoidica: etiology: diabetes mellitus leading to angiopathy histology: palisade get granuloma around a degenerated collagen Clinical features: erythematous papules,plaques,on shins symmetrically distributed, surface smooth waxy shiny. Central atrophy and ulceration with telengiectasia. Most common site of necrobiosis lipoidica diabeticorum Shins. association: diabetes-75% inflammatory bowel disease ,sarcoidosis, an a vasculitis syndromes treatment: intralesional steroids excision and grafting chloroquine control of diabetes has no specific effect on skin Iadvl textbook of dermatology page 1196",
